Cysteine 133 and cysteine 158

2fk3 B 144 E 133

A redox-regulated disulphide may form between two units of Amyloid-beta precursor protein at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.

Peptide name
Amyloid-beta precursor protein

3ktm B 186 B 187

A redox-regulated disulphide may form within Amyloid-beta precursor protein at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.
